snippet.textDisplay:
As someone who has been to Kilve a lot this was rather painful to watch, what with his pronunciation of Kilve (it's not Kilv-a it's simply Kilv), then when it said Kilve many times and he was more focussed on it being near Bath and Bristol, I felt like screaming that he had the answer within the first couple minutes of him being there


*For anyone who doesn't know, Kilve is a little seaside town on the Bristol coast, it's mostly known for its rock pools as the beach is much more a stoney beach than a sandy one, and you're more likely to find dog walkers than tourists. It's also a rather nice place to go for campfires / bonfires as at nighttime you're not likely to get bombarded like other beaches


It's also often used as a residential place for school kids, I myself didn't go but my brother did when he was in year 6

This video was entertaining, but seriously, what's the challenge? It's just a matter of time until, in any city, you will find enough evidence (street names, city name, e.g. on delivery vans or newspapers or company signs or even a letter in a mailbox). Then pull out your smartphone and find the street on the map!
Since this video is edited, what appears to be minutes might have been much longer.
The whole challenge would only be interesting if there was either a time limit or a limited radius of operation - afaik the geoguessr videos have a limited radius.
